			<!-- Begin News/Information Section -->
				<table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" ID="Table23">
					<tr id="trmasthead">
						<td valign="middle" class="main_font" align="center">
							<font size="3"><b>&nbsp;</b></font>
					    </td>
					</tr>
					
					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
  <tr>
    <td valign="top" align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="5">
    Hymn of Restoration</font>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=101"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></td>
    <td valign="top" align="left"><img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/magic.gif" width="216" height="30" align="right">
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2">
    <!--<a href="magic.asp?mode=updateform&amp;ID=101">-->
    <a href="../UserUpdate.asp?ID=101">
    <small><font face="Verdana"><strong>Add New Info Here</strong></font></small>
    </a>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td valign="top" align="left">
		<font face="verdana" size="2">
		<b>Description:</b> <br>
		   There are 3 factors that determine the healing rate of the Hymn of Restoration: sit/stand, sing/string, and exp/skill.<BR>
   Keep in mind that healing rates increase by 1 hp if sitting, and 2 hps if playing a stringed instrument, so that the difference between standing singing and sitting strumming is 3 hps:<BR>
<BR>
<I>Singing:</I><BR>
  Stand - 3 hps<BR>
  Sit - 4 hps<BR>
<I>Strumming:</I><BR>
  Stand - 5 hps<BR>
  Sit - 6 hps<BR>
<BR>
   Additionally, these rates increase with higher skill and experience.<BR>
<BR>
<B>Location:</B> Any Bard Guild<BR>
<B>Skill:</B> Stringed Instruments<BR>
		</font>
	 </td>
	 <td rowspan="4" valign="top" align="right">
    
		<table border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td valign="top" align="left">
