			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I am very confused by what I've read here. I am currently a L10 Bard and here is my experience with the Hymn of Restoration.<BR>
<BR>
-At level 10- you will heal 2HP/tick (approx. 3 sec.) while standing with no instrument.<BR>
<BR>
-At level 10- you will heal 6HP/tick when sitting with a non-magical lute playing.<BR>
<BR>
-At level 10- when I end this song the effects stop at that point, they are no extra pulses after ending the song to twist another. Therefore this spell is not truly twistable (I say this because the effects of this song do not run concurrently with any other song.) Even though the icon remains up in your spell effect window it does not continue you to heal you.<BR>
<BR>
These are solely my experiences and opinions and are not intended to offend or contradict any other posts. This is simply what I believe to be the case.<BR>
<BR>
Elorien, Bard of the 10th Song, Tholuxe Paells<BR>
Maelor, Cleric of the 19th Prayer, Tholuxe Paells<BR>
Icki, Shadow Knight of the 11th Defilement, Tholuxe Paells
				</font>
